    "body": "This problem is still present in 0.16.0, apply does not retain category dtypes.\n\n``` python\nimport pandas\n\ndf = pandas.DataFrame({'col0': [1, 2, 3, 4, 5],\n                       'col1': ['yes', 'no', 'no', 'yes', 'yes'],\n                       'col2': ['small', 'large', 'medium', 'large', 'small']})\ndf['col2'] = pandas.Categorical(df['col2'], categories=['small', 'medium', 'large'],\n                                ordered=True)\n\nother = df.apply(lambda x: x)\n\n# returns category\nprint(df['col2'].dtype)\n# returns object\nprint(other['col2'].dtype)\n```\n\npandas.show_versions():\n\n```\nINSTALLED VERSIONS\n------------------\ncommit: None\npython: 3.4.3.final.0\npython-bits: 64\nOS: Linux\nOS-release: 3.19.1-201.fc21.x86_64\nmachine: x86_64\nprocessor: x86_64\nbyteorder: little\nLC_ALL: None\nLANG: de_DE.utf8\n\npandas: 0.16.0\nnose: 1.3.4\nCython: 0.21.2\nnumpy: 1.9.2\nscipy: 0.15.1\nstatsmodels: 0.6.1\nIPython: 3.0.0\nsphinx: 1.2.3\npatsy: 0.3.0\ndateutil: 2.4.1\npytz: 2015.2\nbottleneck: None\ntables: 3.1.1\nnumexpr: 2.3.1\nmatplotlib: 1.4.3\nopenpyxl: 1.8.5\nxlrd: 0.9.3\nxlwt: None\nxlsxwriter: 0.5.7\nlxml: 3.4.0\nbs4: 4.3.2\nhtml5lib: None\nhttplib2: None\napiclient: None\nsqlalchemy: None\npymysql: None\npsycopg2: None\n```\n"
